  "prompt": "Is calibri with font size 9 good for resume?",
  "response": "Using Calibri with a font size of 9 for a resume is generally considered too small, as it can make the text difficult to read. Typically, a font size of 10 to 12 is recommended for the body text of a resume, with headings slightly larger to create a clear hierarchy and improve readability. Calibri is a modern and professional font, which is suitable for resumes, but it's important to ensure that the text is easily legible for hiring managers. Always print a test copy to check readability or view it on different screens to ensure it appears clear and professional.",
